08:03.700 --> 08:09.700
Melancholy of Lars Von Trier

08:13.900 --> 08:20.200
Part 1 JUSTINE

09:00.700 --> 09:01.700
Sir...

09:07.410 --> 09:11.850
You can back up a little more if you want...
I think you need that extra...

09:11.900 --> 09:14.100
I don't think he can hear you.

09:14.929 --> 09:16.700
Sir, can you hear me up there?

09:18.700 --> 09:20.300
Can you copy, sailor?

09:20.700 --> 09:22.700
I think he's in a different county...

09:24.100 --> 09:25.700
It's like five feet.

09:26.500 --> 09:29.700
And now he stops. He's got five feet here.

09:34.700 --> 09:37.500
That's good. Stop, stop, stop, stop!

10:05.000 --> 10:07.500
Wait, wait, wait!

10:07.700 --> 10:10.700
You're a little close.
I think he can keep going a little bit, maybe.

10:11.288 --> 10:14.390
Oh, no, no, no.
He can't. I don't...

10:19.500 --> 10:21.900
Be careful, please. It is not my car.
I will.

10:22.000 --> 10:23.100
I promise.

10:24.000 --> 10:27.200
Turn around to the left, please.
Stop there, sir.

10:29.950 --> 10:31.050
Straighten up, sir.

10:31.200 --> 10:33.500
Yeah, I think I'm good there, right?

10:34.700 --> 10:36.000
You're not even looking.

10:36.500 --> 10:38.500
I can see it's not looking good.

10:39.582 --> 10:40.582
I'm a very experienced driver...

10:44.000 --> 10:46.700
It's like really close on that side.
Really?

10:46.900 --> 10:49.700
Yeah, don't go any further forward. Just straight...

10:50.200 --> 10:52.000
How do I put it in...?

10:52.700 --> 10:53.900
What?

10:59.713 --> 11:00.713
This way?

11:01.700 --> 11:03.000
Get out of the way.

11:03.200 --> 11:04.700
Come on.

11:08.300 --> 11:09.450
Sorry.

11:18.300 --> 11:19.600
Yes, I know.

11:20.000 --> 11:21.200
We're sorry.

11:21.300 --> 11:24.200
I won't even bother saying how late you are.

11:24.300 --> 11:25.500
Sorry. We're really sorry.

11:27.700 --> 11:29.000
Hi.

11:31.200 --> 11:33.500
Hi, Claire. So sorry.

11:34.000 --> 11:35.000
Hi.

11:35.500 --> 11:37.900
We probably should have taken something smaller.

11:38.500 --> 11:41.700
This brilliant idea was yours of renting a stretch.

11:45.000 --> 11:47.700
This is very much not my project, okay?

11:48.300 --> 11:51.600
I spent the whole week with the dullest man on earth.

11:51.700 --> 11:54.600
Not to mention the most expensive wedding planner
on the planet.

11:55.300 --> 11:57.500
Okay, so you want this?

11:58.100 --> 11:59.500
Yeah, of course.

11:59.700 --> 12:04.200
So, when you're there... and that was two hours ago.

12:04.372 --> 12:05.372
Okay.

12:05.881 --> 12:07.381
All right, let's go.

12:11.000 --> 12:12.700
What star is that?

12:13.100 --> 12:13.740
I don't know.

12:15.500 --> 12:17.900
John, you're a bit of an expert on stars,
aren't you?

12:18.000 --> 12:19.500
I wouldn't say that.

12:19.600 --> 12:20.400
Oh, yes you would.

12:20.600 --> 12:22.700
Which one are you looking at exactly?

12:23.700 --> 12:24.800
The red one.

12:26.700 --> 12:28.565
I'm amazed you can see that.

12:28.600 --> 12:33.200
That's Antares. It's the main star in the
Scorpio constellation.

12:37.500 --> 12:38.700
Justine...

12:39.500 --> 12:41.700
We just have to go to the stables to say hello
to Abraham.

12:41.800 --> 12:43.200
No, you're not.
Oh, yes.

12:43.500 --> 12:44.700
Who's Abraham?

12:52.854 --> 12:53.854
Abraham.

12:55.400 --> 12:57.600
Look, I'm married.

12:58.500 --> 13:00.700
Michael's my husband now.

13:02.200 --> 13:04.600
I'm sure you two will like each other.

13:04.700 --> 13:06.500
Nice to meet you.

13:07.700 --> 13:10.700
I'm his mistress. I'm the only one who can ride him.

13:11.300 --> 13:13.000
That's not exactly true.

13:14.500 --> 13:16.700
What? Occasionally I take her for a ride.

13:17.000 --> 13:18.200
See you later.

13:23.800 --> 13:27.700
I can no longer be silent.
All the guests are waiting for more than two hours.

13:27.800 --> 13:28.550
I know.

13:28.600 --> 13:30.300
I'm at the end of my rope.

13:30.700 --> 13:33.600
Welcome to the reception of Mr. Steinam, Mr. Marko.

13:33.900 --> 13:36.100
Thank you.
Thank you, Little Father.

13:36.700 --> 13:40.100
Would you be so good as to to participate
in the wedding bean lottery?

13:40.400 --> 13:41.000
Of course.

13:46.000 --> 13:50.000
Please submit your bid as to the total number
of beans in the bottle.

13:50.100 --> 13:54.900
Yes, er... two million and six beans.

13:55.100 --> 13:57.500
Two million and six beans.

13:58.000 --> 14:00.600
Would you care to make a bid on behalf of your wife?

14:00.800 --> 14:03.700
Oh, I don't dare to do that.
I really don't.

14:03.900 --> 14:06.600
Very well, we'll let madam's bid remain open.

14:11.600 --> 14:13.000
We made it.

14:26.900 --> 14:28.200
Hi, Mom.

14:28.470 --> 14:29.470
Love that dress.

14:30.200 --> 14:32.800
Congratulations Aunt Steelbreaker.

14:33.000 --> 14:34.200
Thanks, Leo.

14:35.500 --> 14:37.600
What's this?
A dagger.

14:37.734 --> 14:38.734
Wow!

14:43.377 --> 14:44.377
Sweetheart.

14:48.100 --> 14:52.500
Let me introduce you.
This is Betty... and Betty.

14:52.700 --> 14:56.200
Betty and Betty, this is my daughter, Justine.

14:56.250 --> 14:58.500
Hi, nice to meet you.

14:58.700 --> 15:01.500
I'm gonna say hi to everybody.
Of course, of course.

15:03.500 --> 15:05.700
Ladies and gentlemen...

15:06.700 --> 15:11.100
We waited a while for this.
A toast to the bride and the groom.

15:11.700 --> 15:14.200
Justine and Michael.

15:28.700 --> 15:32.100
The tray must go left to right...

15:33.600 --> 15:35.700
From left to right.

15:37.200 --> 15:39.900
Justine, I don't want to make a speech.

15:41.100 --> 15:43.700
Why? Please.

15:47.300 --> 15:48.700
What are you doing?

15:50.200 --> 15:51.600
You'll see.

15:54.700 --> 15:56.200
Excuse me.

16:00.700 --> 16:04.700
Neither of the ladies sitting next to me
has been given a spoon.

16:06.000 --> 16:08.500
I'd like very much to have one.

16:08.700 --> 16:09.600
Excuse me.

16:24.200 --> 16:25.300
You're terrible.

16:25.600 --> 16:26.700
Waiter.

16:27.000 --> 16:31.000
Justine, would you mind slapping your father
for me hard, please.

16:35.500 --> 16:36.500
Tim.

16:41.000 --> 16:43.200
Justine, listen up, goddammit.

16:43.700 --> 16:49.200
As most of you know,
I'm here tonight playing sort of a double role.

16:49.700 --> 16:52.700
On Michael's side, I'm best man.

16:53.000 --> 16:56.200
And, coincidentally, I'm also the employer
of the bride.

16:56.500 --> 16:59.200
I've got nothing bad to say about the groom, but...

16:59.700 --> 17:01.400
The bride...

17:03.500 --> 17:05.099
Justine...

17:05.500 --> 17:07.200
Gorgeous woman...

17:07.700 --> 17:09.700
Where's my tagline?

17:09.800 --> 17:12.500
You were always great in coming up
with a tagline in a hurry.

17:12.700 --> 17:14.099
What happened?

17:14.599 --> 17:17.400
Did your emotional life suddenly take over?

17:17.450 --> 17:21.200
Did finding the man of your life render you
unable to work?

17:21.700 --> 17:25.700
I'm just asking because if I were to choose between

17:25.701 --> 17:29.700
a woman for my dear friend Michael and an employee...

17:30.500 --> 17:32.700
I would always choose the employee.

17:37.900 --> 17:41.100
Advertising, Justine, advertising.

17:41.700 --> 17:46.200
Justine, you were way, way, way too good for advertising.

17:46.700 --> 17:49.800
You know it, I know it, we all know it.

17:50.200 --> 17:52.100
So thank you for staying with it.

17:53.700 --> 17:56.450
I'm gonna let you and the rest of you
think about this tagline now

17:56.451 --> 17:59.200
while I leak a bit of news.

18:00.100 --> 18:04.200
Today the company hasn't lost a copywriter...

18:04.500 --> 18:07.600
The company has gained a new art director.

18:08.100 --> 18:09.700
And that's you, Justine.

18:11.400 --> 18:12.700
Congratulations.

18:13.700 --> 18:15.300
Goddammit, you earned it.

18:23.900 --> 18:26.200
The father of the bride wants a word.

18:39.700 --> 18:45.600
My dear girl, you look...

18:46.700 --> 18:48.600
glowing today.

18:50.000 --> 18:55.600
And me, I'm just a little confused
what with all the Bettys at my table.

18:58.200 --> 19:00.200
Never seen you look so happy.

19:02.700 --> 19:07.100
So, what can say without talking about your mother?

19:08.300 --> 19:10.700
My wife of yesteryear.

19:11.700 --> 19:14.700
Which is exactly what I don't wish to do.

19:15.700 --> 19:20.200
I don't think that I would be revealing any secret
if I were to say

19:20.201 --> 19:24.700
that she can be very domineering at times.

19:25.400 --> 19:26.700
Domineering?

19:27.500 --> 19:28.900
What a load of crap!

19:29.600 --> 19:33.600
For those who don't know who I am,
I'm Claire and Justine's mother.

19:33.700 --> 19:36.800
Justine, if you have any ambition at all,

19:36.979 --> 19:40.149
it certainly doesn't come from your father's
side of the family.

19:42.700 --> 19:43.700
Yes.

19:45.500 --> 19:49.200
I wasn't at the church. I don't believe in marriage.

19:50.700 --> 19:54.450
Claire, whom I have always taken for a sensible girl,

19:54.451 --> 19:58.200
you've arranged a spectacular party.

19:58.700 --> 20:04.100
Till death do us part and forever and ever...
Justine and Michael.

20:05.200 --> 20:07.300
I just have one thing to say...

20:08.100 --> 20:09.600
Enjoy it while it lasts.

20:10.900 --> 20:12.600
I myself hate marriages.

20:12.700 --> 20:13.900
Gaby, please.

20:14.500 --> 20:18.700
Especially when they involve my closest family members.

20:19.700 --> 20:22.200
Why did you even bother coming?

20:44.700 --> 20:46.700
Justine, come with me.

21:03.700 --> 21:09.200
Listen to me. We agreed that you weren't going
to make any scenes tonight.

21:09.600 --> 21:11.000
The don't want any scenes.

21:11.050 --> 21:13.100
No, we don't!

21:13.764 --> 21:14.764
No.

21:16.000 --> 21:18.300
Look at me when I'm talking to you.

21:19.700 --> 21:21.600
But I didn't do anything.

21:23.700 --> 21:25.700
You know what I mean.

21:32.942 --> 21:33.942
Okay.

21:36.915 --> 21:38.115
Okay.

21:42.400 --> 21:44.900
Katherine has demanded the floor.

24:17.300 --> 24:19.000
Where is the bride?

24:20.200 --> 24:21.900
I've looked everywhere, no bride.

24:31.700 --> 24:35.200
Now the groom is going to give a speech for the bride.

24:41.700 --> 24:43.200
Dear Justine...

24:50.900 --> 24:53.700
What are you doing to me?
I've never given a speech before.

24:56.700 --> 25:01.200
I'm serious, I've never given a speech before.

25:01.500 --> 25:05.200
Justine is the speaker.
She can say the most wonderful things, but...

25:05.350 --> 25:07.600
Then let her make the speech, damn it.

25:12.700 --> 25:14.200
Justine...

25:15.700 --> 25:17.700
I love you so much...

25:22.700 --> 25:27.700
And never dreamed that I would have
such a gorgeous wife.

25:32.200 --> 25:36.500
I believe that I'm the luckiest man on Earth.

25:40.200 --> 25:41.500
I love you.

25:46.000 --> 25:48.200
That's kind of it. That's all I have.

25:55.700 --> 25:58.780
Hello, everyone, we're going to move to the living room

25:58.819 --> 26:00.489
so that we can clear some tables.

26:02.000 --> 26:04.500
Then the newlyweds will dance.

26:05.000 --> 26:11.700
And then, at eleven thirty,
the bride and groom will cut the cake in here.

26:46.700 --> 26:48.500
He wants to be put to bed.

26:48.600 --> 26:51.300
Sweety, you did so good.

26:51.400 --> 26:52.500
I wanna do it.

26:52.600 --> 26:55.400
No, tonight's your night.
No, please.

26:56.700 --> 26:59.700
Are you sure?
Yeah, come on.

26:59.800 --> 27:02.600
Good night, sweetheart.
Come on, come here.

27:11.200 --> 27:12.900
Are you comfortable?

27:20.700 --> 27:23.200
When are we gonna build caves together?

27:23.500 --> 27:27.700
We're gonna build lots of caves together.
Just not  tonight.

27:28.300 --> 27:31.100
You're still my aunt Steelbreaker, aren't you?

27:31.500 --> 27:34.000
Yes. It's exactly who I am.

27:51.500 --> 27:52.500
Justine...

27:56.500 --> 27:57.700
Hi, Claire.

27:59.200 --> 28:01.700
I'm just taking a little nap.

28:02.700 --> 28:05.700
Don't nap, it's your wedding.

28:07.700 --> 28:09.700
You're not even halfway through yet.

28:11.700 --> 28:13.200
No. you're right.

28:17.700 --> 28:20.200
I have to pull myself together.

28:28.100 --> 28:30.600
What's going on, Justine?

28:43.700 --> 28:47.600
I'm trudging in through this...

28:48.916 --> 28:53.476
Praying really hard.

28:56.700 --> 28:59.700
It's clinging to my legs.

29:03.200 --> 29:07.200
It's really heavy to drag along.

29:13.400 --> 29:16.700
No, you're not.

29:17.200 --> 29:19.700
I know you'll hate to hear it.

29:28.200 --> 29:30.700
Don't say a word to Michael.

29:33.500 --> 29:35.200
You think I'm stupid?

30:24.900 --> 30:26.400
I'll get her.

30:26.500 --> 30:28.200
And my mom, too.
Yeah.

30:43.700 --> 30:48.000
Justine, It's John.
We're ready to cut the cake, sweetheart.

30:48.700 --> 30:51.100
Please come downstairs as soon as you can, okay?

30:57.900 --> 30:58.700
Gaby...

31:05.100 --> 31:06.100
Gaby...

31:17.700 --> 31:21.100
Gaby, I'm sorry to disturb you,
but we're ready to cut the cake.

31:23.700 --> 31:26.900
When Justine took her first crap on her potty,
I wasn't there.

31:27.700 --> 31:30.900
When she had her first sexual intercourse,
I wasn't there.

31:31.500 --> 31:34.100
So give me a break, please,
with all your fucking rituals.

31:34.200 --> 31:36.100
Unbelievable, fucking unbelievable.

31:38.800 --> 31:41.450
Everyone, thank you for being so patient.

31:41.500 --> 31:45.200
We're just having a little issue with the wedding dress.
She'll be right down.

31:45.700 --> 31:49.800
Those bitches have locked themselves in their bedrooms
and now they're taking a bath.

31:49.900 --> 31:52.700
Is everybody in your family stark raving mad?

31:56.600 --> 31:59.500
This is embarrassing.
I know.

32:02.200 --> 32:06.100
We should have put showers in the guest wing.
I've said it a hundred times.

32:06.200 --> 32:09.800
For fuck's sakes, if people want to linger in a bath,
stay at home.

32:09.850 --> 32:13.725
Here we offer you an 18 hole golf course,
where else would they get that?

32:14.300 --> 32:15.700
Nowhere.

32:18.700 --> 32:19.700
Unbelievable!

32:23.400 --> 32:25.550
That's it, she's out.
What, Justine?

32:25.600 --> 32:26.700
Your mother.

32:47.200 --> 32:48.600
Unbelievable.

33:44.200 --> 33:47.200
She ruined my wedding. I will not look at her.

34:01.700 --> 34:03.200
Outstanding.

34:04.838 --> 34:06.138
My God, we cut it.

34:21.500 --> 34:22.699
I'm sorry.

34:23.600 --> 34:25.900
No, don't say that.

34:27.199 --> 34:29.500
You should never say you're sorry.

34:32.300 --> 34:34.699
I can see that you're not feeling well tonight.

34:35.699 --> 34:38.199
You should have seen you weren't ready yesterday.

34:40.500 --> 34:43.400
I haven't been taking care of you lately.

34:44.199 --> 34:45.600
It's my fault.

34:51.699 --> 34:54.699
Can we talk somewhere?
Of course.

34:56.000 --> 34:57.600
Sit down, please.

34:58.500 --> 35:00.700
I wasn't going to give you this until tomorrow.

35:08.500 --> 35:10.500
I found our plot of land.

35:19.100 --> 35:20.900
They call it Empire apples.

35:22.200 --> 35:24.700
They're bright red and very sweet.

35:25.200 --> 35:27.600
But with the perfect tartness.

35:29.200 --> 35:30.700
I had one as a kid.

35:32.000 --> 35:33.500
Beautiful, huh?

35:34.500 --> 35:39.665
In ten years' time, when the trees have grown
you can sit in the shade, in a chair.

35:39.700 --> 35:43.700
If you still have days when you're feeling a little sad...

35:45.500 --> 35:48.400
I think that will make you happy again.

35:52.500 --> 35:54.100
It's very sweet.

35:54.600 --> 35:55.700
Yeah?

36:00.700 --> 36:03.100
No wonder you've been so busy.

36:04.500 --> 36:07.300
I signed the deed for it yesterday,
I didn't want to tell you.

36:09.700 --> 36:10.700
Here.

36:10.700 --> 36:12.810
No, you should have it,

36:12.850 --> 36:16.110
I want you to have it with you all the time
and hold on to it.

36:16.900 --> 36:20.600
So you can look at it once in a while.

36:23.200 --> 36:25.100
I'll always keep with me.

36:28.800 --> 36:32.700
Maybe we can have a little swing
hanging from one of the trees.

36:35.700 --> 36:38.200
We'll talk about that when the time comes.

36:38.700 --> 36:41.700
Yeah, no... of course.

36:42.500 --> 36:44.400
When the time comes.

37:12.700 --> 37:14.200
Goodbye.

37:44.200 --> 37:46.700
You'd better be goddamn happy.

37:49.800 --> 37:52.200
Yes, I should be.

37:53.150 --> 37:54.550
I really should be.

37:54.600 --> 37:58.700
Do you have any idea how much this party cost me?
A ballpark figure?

37:58.817 --> 37:59.817
No.

38:01.200 --> 38:03.100
I don't.

38:05.700 --> 38:08.400
Should I?
Yes, I think you should.

38:08.900 --> 38:10.500
A great deal of money.

38:11.200 --> 38:13.500
A huge amount of money.

38:14.200 --> 38:17.600
In fact, for most people, an arm and a leg.

38:20.600 --> 38:23.100
I hope you feel it's well spent.

38:23.200 --> 38:26.700
Well, that depends on whether or not we have a deal.

38:29.000 --> 38:31.800
A deal?
Yes, a deal.

38:32.900 --> 38:35.100
That you'll be happy.

38:38.900 --> 38:42.100
Yes, of course. Of course we have a deal.

38:42.700 --> 38:43.600
Good.

38:45.000 --> 38:46.600
Congratulations.

38:47.700 --> 38:49.900
I tried to throw your mother out.

38:50.500 --> 38:53.100
Yes, you usually do.

38:55.700 --> 38:57.800
Yes, I do.

38:59.700 --> 39:00.900
Thank you.

39:02.700 --> 39:05.200
It's a wonderful party you've given me.

39:06.000 --> 39:08.150
How many holes are on our golf course?

39:08.500 --> 39:09.200
Eighteen.

39:09.600 --> 39:11.000
That's right.

39:38.000 --> 39:41.400
Happy? Yeah.

39:46.500 --> 39:48.400
This is the young man.

39:48.600 --> 39:51.000
Congratulations.
Thank you.

39:51.100 --> 39:53.100
I'm Tim.
Hi, Tim.

39:53.300 --> 39:55.100
Tim started working for us two days ago.

39:55.150 --> 39:57.000
He happens to be my nephew, but ignore that.

39:57.100 --> 40:00.500
Tim thought I wouldn't be able to squeeze that tagline
out of you tonight.

40:00.700 --> 40:03.300
I thought it might be difficult.

40:03.500 --> 40:07.700
You're colleagues. I hired him the moment I heard
about his education.

40:09.700 --> 40:13.250
What education is perfect if you want to make it
in Public Relations?

40:16.500 --> 40:17.300
Tim?

40:18.600 --> 40:20.650
None at all, of course.

40:20.700 --> 40:22.600
It was almost too perfect.

40:22.900 --> 40:25.700
He knows nothing. I hired him on the spot.

40:26.000 --> 40:29.000
And at a very good salary. What do you say, Tim?

40:29.200 --> 40:31.700
A very good salary.

40:32.700 --> 40:34.700
Welcome, then, Tim.

40:35.200 --> 40:39.450
There's just a slight catch
to a very good job with a very good salary.

40:39.500 --> 40:41.500
The salary is very good.

40:42.500 --> 40:44.850
Why, what are you pushing Tim into doing?

40:44.900 --> 40:47.500
To get that damn tagline out of you tonight.

40:47.700 --> 40:52.000
Otherwise he's out on his ear, which sucks,
considering the debts he's in.

40:52.100 --> 40:52.900
Goodbye.

40:54.500 --> 40:56.500
Once you give her a job, she won't let go.

40:56.550 --> 40:59.600
You gotta be there at the time of birth,
so you follow her now.

40:59.650 --> 41:02.100
I mean, get that tagline.

41:33.800 --> 41:37.000
Do let me know if the tagline's there
and I'll jot it down.

41:38.100 --> 41:39.500
Spare me.

41:50.700 --> 41:53.500
I'll go out for a minute.

41:58.500 --> 41:59.700
I'm really sorry.

41:59.800 --> 42:04.200
I'm thrilled about this wedding
and I know it's costing John a lot of money.

42:04.700 --> 42:08.700
John's filthy mouth...
He needs to shut up about it.

42:09.300 --> 42:11.200
It 's not about the cost.

