Don't worry about it.

46:46.100 --> 46:47.700
Dad, can we talk?

51:19.000 --> 51:21.100
Could you sit with me for a little while?

51:55.200 --> 51:56.900
Wait. What?

51:59.500 --> 52:00.600
Wait.

52:01.800 --> 52:03.200
Get out of me.

52:05.000 --> 52:07.500
Michael, can you give me a moment?
What's happened?

52:08.100 --> 52:10.200
Just give me a moment, please.
What's happened?

52:13.700 --> 52:15.600
Can I have a moment, please?

52:17.700 --> 52:20.900
Yeah... of course.

52:27.200 --> 52:28.600
Can you zip me?

52:41.300 --> 52:42.600
Are you okay?

52:43.951 --> 52:44.951
Okay.

53:36.200 --> 53:37.400
Hi.

54:43.700 --> 54:45.600
Good night. Have a good time.

54:46.100 --> 54:48.100
I'm on my way home, my darling.

54:49.300 --> 54:52.700
Please, Dad, I really need to talk to you.

54:56.100 --> 54:57.300
Little Father...

54:59.700 --> 55:03.500
My dad would like to spend the night.
Is there a room available?

55:03.900 --> 55:06.500
Room number eight is vacant.

55:07.500 --> 55:09.665
We could prepare that for your father.

55:09.700 --> 55:12.500
Well ..
Yes, my father likes that.

55:13.600 --> 55:15.700
Then we can have breakfast in the morning.

55:45.800 --> 55:48.700
Justine...

55:49.000 --> 55:51.700
Why don't you come and have onion soup with us?

55:57.300 --> 55:59.300
Tim. Get us some soup.

56:04.200 --> 56:06.200
How's your wonderful night going?

56:15.800 --> 56:17.700
It's too bad about Tim.

56:18.500 --> 56:20.200
What about Tim?

56:21.500 --> 56:23.200
He got fired.

56:24.700 --> 56:27.600
He didn't last many hours in the business, but...

56:27.650 --> 56:32.500
then again, it's a rather unpredictable one,
you're king one day and beggar the next.

56:33.700 --> 56:36.500
So you go back to wherever you came from,
right buddy?

56:39.300 --> 56:43.700
I'm glad we found each other, Jack.
I was looking for you.

56:45.700 --> 56:50.100
Didn't I tell you? She can't stop working,
not even on your wedding night.

56:50.700 --> 56:53.700
I had nothing at the dinner...

56:54.200 --> 56:59.200
But I've been playing with an idea for a small campaign.

56:59.500 --> 57:03.400
The problem is, how do we effectively hook
a group of minors

57:03.451 --> 57:05.700
on our substandard product,

57:06.200 --> 57:08.800
preferably in a habit-forming way?

57:09.500 --> 57:12.700
And I've reached a conclusion in regards to the tagline.

57:13.600 --> 57:16.220
I was just thinking, what if...

57:16.272 --> 57:18.102
instead...

57:17.300 --> 57:23.000
we try to sell you to the public, Jack?

57:25.700 --> 57:30.300
Then, surprisingly,
I arrived right back where I started from.

57:31.400 --> 57:32.700
At nothing.

57:33.900 --> 57:36.900
Nothing? It's not such a bad tagline, Jack.

57:40.700 --> 57:45.700
Would my newly fledged aide please
expand a little on the thoughts of the tagline?

57:49.000 --> 57:51.700
Nothing is too much for you, Jack.

57:53.700 --> 57:57.600
I hate you and your firm so deeply

57:57.601 --> 58:01.500
I couldn't find the words to describe it.

58:03.100 --> 58:09.200
You are a despicable, power-hungry little man, Jack.

58:13.400 --> 58:15.500
Is that a resignation?

58:15.550 --> 58:18.800
'Cause there aren't too many jobs out there,
I tell you.

58:31.500 --> 58:32.900
I broke my plate.

59:15.500 --> 59:16.900
So I...

59:17.700 --> 59:18.770
I guess we'll...

59:20.535 --> 59:21.735
take off now.

59:30.200 --> 59:31.500
Yes.

59:35.200 --> 59:37.700
This could have been a lot different.

59:43.500 --> 59:46.200
Yes, Michael, that have been.

59:56.500 --> 59:58.300
But, Michael...

01:00:00.700 --> 01:00:02.700
what did you expect?

01:00:08.200 --> 01:00:09.700
Yeah.

01:00:14.700 --> 01:00:16.200
You're right.

01:00:37.600 --> 01:00:38.900
Claire...

01:00:42.200 --> 01:00:45.200
Sometimes, I hate you so much.

01:00:56.100 --> 01:01:00.600
